title: John C. Calhoun
deleted: In 2020 the University of Connecticut erected a monument to celebrate the venerated coach’s multiple NCAA National championships during his tenure as men’s head basketball coach. Coach Calhoun, always the southern firebrand, once famously said “my only regret is being this damned good at a school plum in the middle of so much Yankee scum. That’s life. There’s nothing in life that’s fair. I’m sarrr.”
